- !<Text/191481a1-06c8-4250-b793-614732e3abdb>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: Text
  Enabled: true
  RenderOrder: 999
  StretchMode: Stretch
  VerticalAlignment: Center
  HorizontalAlignment: Left
  MeshShadowMode: None
  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |-
    DJ Specs
    
    This highly customized project by artist Yurii Roznatovskyi demonstrates how to build a DJ Lens that lets users mix their favorite audio tracks in an interactive way.
    The codebase is available in TS and JS. 
    
    
    How It Works
    
    Start the experience with an empty space or table in front of you.
    
    Select a track from the list on your right by pointing and pinching one of the circular buttons.
    
    Load the track by grabbing (or pinch-pointing) the record and placing it onto the deck.
    
    Adjust the playback speed using the vertical slider.
    
    Control the crossfade with the slider located at the center of the console.
    
    Enjoy your DJ set!
    
    Important Note
    
    All audio tracks are pre-processed when the Lens loads. This may take a few seconds before the experience is fully ready.
    
    Technical Details
    
    This project includes a custom audio library for advanced pitch control and audio playback management.
